From adc6fa71f8b5bb5c7530926aa79ce28f34f10456 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 05:14:06 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] refactor(sidebar): replace fake phase progress with real
 navigation

The sidebar module header showed a hardcoded 28% progress bar and a phase
list whose done/active/locked states were faked by index, navigating
nowhere. Removed the misleading progress bar and wired the phase list to a
new store field (learnPhase) shared with the Aprender tab strip, so:

- the active phase is real and reflected consistently in both controls
- clicking a phase enters Aprender at that phase (onOpenPhase -> learn mode)
- no more fake completion checkmarks or locks
